        "paragraph_index": 1,
        "text": "### Why?\n\nNIST SRD-46 (the **NIST Critically Selected Stability Constants of Metal Complexes** database) is focused on **aqueous-phase** equilibrium thermodynamics. It curates critically evaluated log β values for metal–ligand complexes in water, typically at controlled temperature and ionic strength.\n\nStability constant measurements in supercritical CO₂ are quite rare in the broader literature and tend to appear in specialized extraction/separation studies (e.g., chelation of lanthanides or actinides with fluorinated β-diketones in scCO₂). Such data would more likely be found in:\n\n- Primary research articles (e.g., journals like *The Journal of Supercritical Fluids*)\n- Specialized databases for supercritical fluid chemistry\n\n**Source:** NIST Standard Reference Database 46 (SRD-46).",
